📌 Fake Exam Proctor
🧠 Overview

Fake Exam Proctor is a web-based application that simulates an online exam monitoring system. It tracks user behavior during an exam and detects suspicious activities such as tab switching, inactivity, and unusual interactions.

🎯 Features
👁️ Detects tab switching using Page Visibility API
⏳ Tracks user inactivity
🖱️ Monitors user interactions (clicks/events)
⚠️ Displays warnings for suspicious behavior
🔒 Option to disable exam after multiple violations
⚙️ Technologies Used
HTML
CSS
JavaScript
🧩 How It Works
User starts the exam
System begins monitoring activity
If user switches tab → warning triggered
If user remains inactive → alert displayed
After multiple violations → exam is restricted/disabled
🧠 Concepts Used
DOM Manipulation
Event Handling (click, visibilitychange)
Timers (setInterval, setTimeout)
Conditional Logic
Browser APIs (Page Visibility API)
🚀 Future Improvements
Webcam-based face detection (AI integration)
Backend integration for storing logs
Real-time monitoring dashboard
Auto submission on rule violation
🎯 Use Case

This project demonstrates how browser events and user interaction tracking can be used to simulate real-time monitoring systems in online examinations.
